What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Blood Meal Fertilizers Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Blood Meal Fertilizers Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the blood meal fertilizers market will project a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 7.70% during the forecast period of 2021-2028. Growing demand to control various crop related diseases, rising demand for new and mechanized techniques for farming or agriculture especially in the developing countries, growing demand for meat products especially in the developing economies, rising integration of advanced technology with the agricultural equipment and increasing industry competitiveness are the major factors attributable to the growth of blood meal fertilizers market. This means that the blood meal fertilizers market value, which was USD 5.40 billion in 2020 will climb up to USD 9.77 billion by the year 2028.

A large amount of blood is wasted when the animals are slaughtered. Blood meal is a rich source of nitrogen and protein. Therefore, blood meal can be utilized as nitrogen amendment to improve the soil health. In other words, blood meal fertilizers are used to raise the level of nitrogen which in turn improves the agricultural productivity and crop health.

Growing prevalence of parasitic infections and other crop related diseases, rising production of feed, growing preferences towards aquaculture products and increased focus on the research and development proficiencies will emerge as the major factors fostering the growth of the market. Also, growing demand for effective and efficient crop protection tools to improve the crop productivity coupled with growing awareness regarding protein and nitrogen supplements is another important factor fostering the growth of the market. Growth in the demand for fruit and vegetable food items, cereals and grains and others owing to ever-rising population and rising globalization will further create lucrative and remunerative growth opportunities for the market.

However, rising concerns in regards to the conservation of environment coupled with growing awareness about the harmful effects on soil health owing to excessive use of agrochemicals is a major factor that will pose a major challenge to the growth of the market. Also, stringent regulations imposed by the government on the use of agrochemicals and volatility in the prices of raw materials will further slowdown the market growth rate.

